parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause a significant reduction in visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights suddenly shut off
the headlights fail to respond
the headlights dim
the headlights go out briefly
the headlights do not illuminate correctly
the headlights do not come on at all
the headlights only work on low beam
the headlights only work on high beam
the headlights flicker
the headlights are intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the headlights, interior lights, and instrument panel lights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights
interior lights
and instrument panel lights malfunction or fail
sudden loss of lights while driving
inability to read gauges or speedometer
and loud humming noise from the alternator.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal and Brake Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the turn signal and brake lights can cause accidents or near-misses due to reduced visibility and communication with other drivers.
symptoms: Turn signal lights do not function
brake lights do not function
and flashing and clicking sounds when using turn signals.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Difficulty turning the key in the ignition switch
alarm security warning light illuminates
and sudden loss of engine power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag and horn systems can cause accidents or injuries due to reduced safety features and warning systems.
symptoms: Horn button shorts out and the horn blows continuously
requiring fuse removal to stop
and airbag system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden unintended acceleration can cause accidents or near-misses due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often when slowing down or stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is engaged
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes produce a loud grinding noise
the brakes squeal or make a loud noise when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake cylinders can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: The brakes produce a loud grinding noise
the brakes squeal or make a loud noise when applied
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents, loss of control, or extended stopping distances.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brakes produce a loud grinding noise
the brakes squeal or make a loud noise when applied
the vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locks can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential theft.
symptoms: The doors lock and unlock intermittently
the doors fail to lock or unlock using the remote key entry device
the trunk pops open while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tires can cause accidents, loss of control, or blowouts.
symptoms: The tread separates
the tires need to be replaced frequently.
